&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fluency, we come together under two shared passions that drive our culture: the scaling of digital ad operations, and fostering a workplace environment rooted in open communication, inclusivity, and a growth-oriented mindset. These passions not only set us apart in the industry, but also fuel our collective drive to reshape the industry and reinvent ourselves along the way. We&#39;re not just revolutionizing the digital advertising horizon, we&#39;re shaping an organization where every member feels a sense of pride and is inspired to do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a passionate, detail-obsessed team building the next generation of AI-native enterprise software. We turn complex ad-tech into intuitive, conversational experiences. We need a design leader to guide our small team through this transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Manager, Product Design leads a team of designers while staying hands-on. You will steer our design direction as we evolve from form-driven interfaces to conversational, AI-powered experiences. This role blends people management—mentoring, coaching, and balancing workloads—with high-impact individual contribution. You will partner with product and engineering to simplify enterprise advertising, while fostering a high-trust, growth-oriented team culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and grow a team of product designers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align design priorities with the product roadmap and business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run design critiques and maintain a high-quality bar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide team clarity and shield them from noise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for design’s impact on product strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design &amp;amp; Craft&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end design for key product surfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design AI-native patterns: conversational UX, progressive disclosure, and intent-driven workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define how the platform communicates system intelligence, recommendations, and uncertainty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evolve our design system to support current and future product surfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex ad-tech into accessible, intuitive experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align design decisions with business goals like retention and competitive growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product and Engineering to shape product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data-driven insights and user-centered design to guide decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearly present design rationale and trade-offs to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales, Client Success, and Marketing to ensure a cohesive customer journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct design reviews and QA to ensure execution matches design intent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Look For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in product design, with 2+ years managing or leading designers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enterprise SaaS product design experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of shipping complex products that users describe as simple&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing for AI-powered, conversational, or agent-driven interfaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Figma; comfort with prototyping tools and design systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-directed; can identify the highest-leverage design problems

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fluency, we come together under two shared passions that drive our culture: the scaling of digital ad operations, and fostering a workplace environment rooted in open communication, inclusivity, and a growth-oriented mindset. These passions not only set us apart in the industry, but also fuel our collective drive to reshape the industry and reinvent ourselves along the way. We&#39;re not just revolutionizing the digital advertising horizon, we&#39;re shaping an organization where every member feels a sense of pride and is inspired to do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Principal Product Manager for Paid Search and AI Search Advertising, you are a deep domain specialist who owns the most mature, complex, and high-impact surface area of Fluency&#39;s platform. You will be the definitive internal expert on search-platform mechanics, likely having owned the product on the system side of a major search platform (such as Google Ads or Microsoft Advertising).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a blend of high-level product strategy, technical depth, and the disciplined management of a partner-driven roadmap. You will bridge the daily reality of technical API requirements with proactive investments in next-generation, AI-driven search environments. You will shape how Fluency&#39;s platform helps enterprise brands and agencies manage billions in ad spend across traditional search and emerging conversational AI interfaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Will Work With&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fluency, Product and Engineering operate in highly collaborative, lean pods to minimize bureaucracy and maximize shipping velocity. In this role, you will lead the Paid Search &amp;amp; Automation Pod, which is composed of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You, acting as the Principal PM and strategic anchor for the surface area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team of 4–6 specialized Software Engineers (spanning backend architecture and API integration specialists) and a dedicated Engineering Lead.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct, recurring collaboration with a designated Product Designer (UX/UI) and a Product Marketing Manager to drive feature adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the end-to-end vision, strategy, and roadmap execution for Fluency’s Search and AI Search Advertising integrations, with Google Ads and Microsoft Advertising at the core.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simultaneously manage reactive, deadline-driven integration maintenance dictated by partner API update and deprecation cycles, while proactively making the case for long-term internal investments that compound over multi-quarter horizons.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply collaborate with your engineering pod to translate complex partner roadmaps into actionable internal plans, navigating architecture conversations at scale and championing invisible maintenance work that protects platform reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Fluency’s execution against emerging AI-driven surfaces, including Performance Max, Demand Gen, ads in ChatGPT, Copilot, and AI Overviews, while designing test programs with strategic agency and enterprise brand customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner across Sales, Client Services, and Product Marketing on positioning, enablement, and customer-facing implications of roadmap decisions, leading through influence and clear, evidence-based product definitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct deep-dive opportunity sizing and competitive research to anticipate how foundational shifts in the search ecosystem will impact our clients before they land.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize product requirements through the eyes of the operator using Fluency every day, the agency executive whose P&amp;amp;L depends on us,

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fluency, we come together under two shared passions that drive our culture: the scaling of digital ad operations, and fostering a workplace environment rooted in open communication, inclusivity, and a growth-oriented mindset. These passions not only set us apart in the industry, but also fuel our collective drive to reshape the industry and reinvent ourselves along the way. We&#39;re not just revolutionizing the digital advertising horizon, we&#39;re shaping an organization where every member feels a sense of pride and is inspired to do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fluency Engineering Team is detail-oriented and extraordinarily passionate about digital advertising. We blend the art and science of advertising into simple and scalable solutions to complex problems, and deliver leading-edge software products to our customers. Our culture is rooted in open communication, inclusivity, and a growth-oriented mindset as we reshape the digital advertising horizon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fluency operates at the scale of $3B+ in annualized media spend across more than 250,000 campaigns per month. The DSP Integrations team is responsible for the technical relationship between Fluency&#39;s automation platform and the major Demand-Side Platforms we integrate with: The Trade Desk, Amazon DSP, and Basis today, with additional DSP and retail-media-network partners on our roadmap. This team is a central piece of Fluency&#39;s strategic position as a gateway through which agents, brands, and agencies reach the full paid media ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fluency platform is built using a native &lt;strong&gt;AWS architecture&lt;/strong&gt;, leveraging &lt;strong&gt;Java&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Spring Boot&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;RDS/MySQL&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;S3&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Vue.js&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Principal Software Engineer, DSP Integrations&lt;/strong&gt; is a full-time remote role with an optional office in Burlington, VT. This is a senior individual contributor role focused on the architecture and execution of Fluency&#39;s integrations with major Demand-Side Platforms, with a near-term focus on accelerating Amazon DSP delivery and sustaining cross-DSP integration depth across TTD, Amazon DSP, and Basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DSP Integrations team does not build a DSP. We build the integration layer between Fluency&#39;s automation platform and the DSPs our customers use. As the Principal Engineer on this team, you will be the senior technical voice on integration architecture, partner API design, and the encoding of each DSP&#39;s distinctive operational semantics into Fluency&#39;s platform. You will work alongside the team&#39;s tech lead and engineers, contributing architectural depth and hands-on execution rather than people leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architect&lt;/strong&gt; Fluency&#39;s integrations with major Demand-Side Platforms (currently TTD, Amazon DSP, and Basis; expanding over time).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design and own partner API integrations&lt;/strong&gt; (REST and GraphQL), including authentication, rate limits, retries, idempotency, reporting feeds, and webhook patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
