&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fluency, we come together under two shared passions that drive our culture: the scaling of digital ad operations, and fostering a workplace environment rooted in open communication, inclusivity, and a growth-oriented mindset. These passions not only set us apart in the industry, but also fuel our collective drive to reshape the industry and reinvent ourselves along the way. We&#39;re not just revolutionizing the digital advertising horizon, we&#39;re shaping an organization where every member feels a sense of pride and is inspired to do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Job Summary&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Digital Advertising Strategist (internally known as an Advertising Engineer) is a highly technical digital advertising expert who bridges the gap between sophisticated ad operations and business-level strategy. Serving as the primary point of contact between Fluency and our clients, you are integral to delivering a world-class client experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fluency, our commitment to value-driven client service is rooted in ideation, creativity, relationships, and strategy. In this role, you will curate the client experience by managing key stakeholder relationships, and proactively implementing Fluency’s capabilities to solve complex business challenges. You will not just manage campaigns; you will drive client business goals, solve operational hurdles through our platform, and identify opportunities to maximize Fluency’s impact on their bottom line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Hybrid Skill Set:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a unique blend of operational leadership and technical execution:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to nurture relationships with C-suite stakeholders, manage complex project timelines, and lead cross-organizational collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A deep technical mastery of building, managing, and optimizing large-scale digital marketing campaigns (Search, Social, Display) to deliver performance at scale without the need for manual coding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Client Engagement &amp;amp; Strategy&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Advertising Architect to lead seamless client transitions and platform integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own post-onboarding relationships at all levels of the client organization, acting as a trusted advisor and platform expert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide expert guidance and training to users on how to leverage the Fluency platform both tactically and operationally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply analyze client business, financial, and operational profiles to recommend opportunities for growth, performance improvement, and business efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage the Fluency platform to execute sophisticated advertising strategies and analyze performance across various channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead high-level strategy calls, weekly syncs, and Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Potential for quarterly travel to visit key clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Internal Collaboration &amp;amp; Product Impact&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal stakeholders to report on client sentiment, requests, and technical hurdles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute client-specific engagement strategies to ensure long-term retention and success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Articulate client growth opportunities and platform feature requests to the Product organization, contributing to the future of the Fluency platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage technical tickets and platform feedback loops to ensure a frictionless client experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What We Look For:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of (5) years of hands-on experience managing complex paid media campaigns (Search, Social, and/or Display).&lt;/li&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fluency, we come together under two shared passions that drive our culture: the scaling of digital ad operations, and fostering a workplace environment rooted in open communication, inclusivity, and a growth-oriented mindset. These passions not only set us apart in the industry, but also fuel our collective drive to reshape the industry and reinvent ourselves along the way. We&#39;re not just revolutionizing the digital advertising horizon, we&#39;re shaping an organization where every member feels a sense of pride and is inspired to do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Enterprise Solutions Director is a high-visibility role that engages with both internal teams and prospective clients. With a deep understanding of the digital marketing landscape, advertising strategies, and Fluency’s platform, this position requires the ability to simplify complex concepts for executives while also diving into the technical details with execution teams. The Director will drive Fluency&#39;s client acquisition efforts by proactively cold calling, managing inbound leads, and securing new clients to expand the customer base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;External Role Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and nurture relationships with new prospective clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the Fluency Platform to key stakeholders across various levels, including users, directors, managers, and executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop compelling business cases to support Fluency’s implementation within prospective client organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a consistent follow-up and outreach routine to generate new business opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Close new business and secure long-term client relationships.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Role Duties: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and maintain a sales pipeline, keeping Executives informed of progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the voice of the customer, providing valuable insights to internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of onboarding guides and best practices.&lt;br&gt;Organize, support, and drive efforts to ensure successful client onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide input on internal education regarding digital marketing strategies and industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Advertising Engineers to ensure a smooth transition from client acquisition to project launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Look For:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong drive for success and goal achievement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise and thought leadership in Digital Advertising, including PPC, Facebook, and Display advertising.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in developing and closing enterprise-level business deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional public speaking and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open to feedback, with a continuous desire to adapt and grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for collaborating with peers and contributing to team success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fluency is headquartered in Burlington, Vermont. This is a full-time, remote position that requires legal authorization to work in the U.S. If you&#39;re local to the area, you&#39;re welcome to work from our office.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At Fluency, we’re proud to be an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re committed to building a diverse, inclusive, and supportive workplace where everyone can thrive. We welcome applicants of all backgrounds and identities and do not tolerate discrimination or harassment of any kind.&lt;/em&gt
